SIMPLE: faithless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faithless
<hw>Faith"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not believing; not
giving credit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be not <qex>faithless</qex>, but believing.</q> <rj><qau>John xx.
27.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not believing on God or religion; specifically, not
believing in the Christian religion.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not observant of promises or covenants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Not true to allegiance, duty, or vows; perfidious;
trecherous; disloyal; not of true fidelity; inconstant, as a husband or
a wife.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A most unnatural and <qex>faithless</qex> service.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Serving to disappoint or deceive; delusive;
unsatisfying.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Yonder <xex>faithless</xex> phantom.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Faith"less*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos><wf>Faith"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Faitour</ent>⟦br⟧
